==English==

===Etymology===
Hebrew ''ba'al'' [[lord]], master, owner.

===Noun===
Hebrew plural: Baalim.

#(''[[Mythology]]'') The [[supreme]] [[male]] [[divinity]] of the [[Phoenicia]]n and [[Canaan]]itish nations. The name of this god occurs in the [[Old Testament]] and elsewhere with qualifying epithets subjoined, answering to the different ideas of his character; as, '''Baal'''-berith, '''Baal'''-zebub, etc.
# The god of "rain, thunder and lightning."
#''[[plural]]'' The whole class of divinities to whom the name Baal was applied. ''Judges x. 6.''
#One of the fallen angels of Satan.
#Any of a class of Medierranean deities whose worship was characterized by the extreme sexual acts of its subjects during periodic celebrations.